condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :I.A.2.a. | Description :The Recipientshall maintain, at all times until the completion of the Project, aNationalSteering Committee, with a composition, mandate and resourcessatisfactory to the Association | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :I.A.3.a. | Description :The Recipient shall maintain at all times until the completion of the Projecta PCUwithin the MEPRI, with staff, terms ofreference, mandate and resources satisfactory to IDA | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :I.A.4. | Description :The Recipient shall maintain at all times until the completion of the ProjectRegionalAdvisors and Facilitators with terms of reference and mandate satisfactory to IDA | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :II.A.1.a. | Description :The Recipient shall prepare Project Reports to cover the period of six calendar months,and shall be furnished to IDA not later than one month after the end of the period coveredby such report | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :II.B.2. | Description :The Recipient shall prepare quarterly Interim unaudited Financial Reports fortheProject and furnish them to IDA not later than 45 days afterthe end of each quarter | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :II.B.3. | Description :The Recipient shall have its Financial Statements audited during every Fiscal Year. Theaudits shall be furnished to the Association not later than six months after theend of such period. | Frequency :Yearly
Hire external auditors for the project, in accordance with the provisions of Section III of Schedule 2 to the Original FinancingAgreement.
